If the RPi creates a wave of kids enthralled with embedded systems and Linux system development, I&#x27;m certainly for it.<p>But, from my viewpoint as an embedded systems developer, I fear that those are greatly steeper learning curves than how the Apple generation (myself included) got started:<p><pre><code>    ]10 PRINT &quot;HELLO WORLD  &quot;;
    ]20 GOTO 10
    ]RUN</code></pre>
